    {
      "title": "Top Scoring NBA Playoffs Star Faces Team Elimination_Knicks_The_-win",
      "link": "https://www.sohu.com/a/892166225_122342248",
      "snippet": "The NBA Playoffs have reached a fever pitch, with the first round drawing to a close. Amidst the chaos, one player has emerged as the standout scorer, but his team's journey may soon come to an abrupt end. Jalen Brunson of the New York Knicks has been nothing short of phenomenal, leading his team to the Eastern Conference semi-finals. However, as they prepare to face the defending champion Boston Celtics, the odds are stacked against them. The New York Knicks' Playoff Journey The New York Knicks entered the playoffs with a respectable 51-win season, a marked improvement from their previous campaigns. Many had written them off as pretenders, but their performance in the first round proved otherwise. Facing the Detroit Pistons, the Knicks battled through a grueling six-game series, with Brunson delivering a series-clinching 40-point performance in Game 6. Despite some fortunate breaks, including a controversial referee 'no call,' the Knicks demonstrated resilience and determination. Brun",
